  "contentHtml": "\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <p><img src=\"https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/et-default-user.svg\" alt=\"Sri Krishna Kummara\">\n                                            \n                                        </p>\n                                                                        \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                    <li>\n                                                                                                                                                                            <a>Sri Krishna Kummara</a>\n                                                            \n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                            </li>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Published On Jul 11, 2026 at 09:12 PM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                </ul>\n                                    \n                                                                            \n                                                                        \n                                \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Vijaywada: Four years after <a href=\"/tag/andhra+pradesh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Andhra Pradesh</a> reported its last <a href=\"/tag/covid-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Covid-19</a> death, two people succumbed to the virus, and four others tested positive in <a href=\"/tag/kadapa+district\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Kadapa district</a> on Thursday, prompting the local <a href=\"/tag/medical+and+health+department\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">medical and health department</a> to step up surveillance in the region.Three of the four people who tested positive for the virus are in home isolation, while the fourth, who is experiencing mild symptoms, has been admitted to a local hospital in Kadapa. “The patient is being treated in a Covid-19 special ward at the hospital,” sources said.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>“All four patients tested positive for Covid-19 during <a href=\"/tag/rt-pcr+tests\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">RT-PCR tests</a> conducted at the Kadapa virology laboratory,” the sources said, adding, “The four positive cases are from different localities in Kadapa. They had also received two doses of the Covid-19 vaccine, while one of them had taken a booster dose too.”</p>\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>Of the two deaths, the first occurred on June 28 at <a href=\"/tag/cmc+vellore\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CMC Vellore</a>. A 60-year-old patient, who was initially admitted to SVIMS in Tirupati and later shifted to CMC Vellore, died while undergoing treatment and subsequently tested positive for Covid-19 through an RT-PCR test. In the second case, a 43-year-old patient receiving treatment also succumbed to the infection after testing positive for the virus.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>“The patient who died at CMC Vellore had diabetes, kidney disease and other comorbidities, while the health records of the second deceased were not available,” the source said. “Based on the symptoms exhibited by the four patients, the <a href=\"/tag/omicron+variant\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Omicron variant</a> is suspected to be responsible for the infections,” the source added.</p><p>Samples of the deceased patients were sent to the National Institute of Virology (NIV), Pune, for <a href=\"/tag/genome+sequencing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">genome sequencing</a> to determine the variant responsible for the infection. It may be recalled that AP last reported a Covid-19 death in 2022.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Sri Krishna Kummara</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Sri Krishna Kummara</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Jul 11, 2026 at 09:12 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Jul 11, 2026 at 09:12 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join the community of 2M+ industry professionals. </h2>   \n                <h3>Subscribe to Newsletter to get latest insights &amp; analysis in your inbox.</h3>\n            <p></p>\n\n            <!-- <figure class=\"top-newsletter-subs__icon-nl\" role=\"presentation\" aria-label=\"Newsletter icon\">\n                <img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://st.etb2bimg.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/icon-newsletter.svg\" alt=\"Newsletter icon\" width=\"55\" height=\"55\">\n            </figure> -->\n        \n            \n                \n                    <h2>All about ETHealthworld industry right on your smartphone! </h2>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><a href=\"/app\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Download the ETHealthworld App</a> and get the Realtime updates and Save your favourite articles.</li>\n                    </ul>\n                                            <!